@startuml ViewStepByDish

actor "User" as User
actor "Admin" as Admin
boundary "DishDetailPage" as View #lightblue
participant ":stepRoute" as Route #lightblue
control "stepController" as Controller #lightblue
participant ":stepService" as Service #lightblue
entity "stepModel" as Model #lightblue
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB #yellow

group View Step Details By Dish
User -> View: 1. Click View Steps for Dish
activate View
View -> Route: 2. GET /api/v1/step/by-dish/:dishId?sortBy=stepNumber&order=asc
activate Route

Route -> Controller: 3. getDetailsByDishId(req, res)
activate Controller

Controller -> Service: 4. getDetailsByDishId(dishId, sortBy, order)
activate Service

Service -> Model: 5. getDetailsByDishId(dishId, sortBy, order)
activate Model

Model -> MongoDB: 6. ExecuteQuery()
activate MongoDB

MongoDB --> Model: 7. Return step list for dish
deactivate MongoDB

Model --> Service: 8. Return steps array
deactivate Model

Service --> Controller: 9. Return steps data
deactivate Service

Controller --> Route: 10. Send JSON response (200, steps data)
deactivate Controller

Route --> View: 11. Render step list
deactivate Route

View --> User: 12. Show step details for dish
deactivate View
end

@enduml